org.liris.smartgov.simulator.urban.osm.environment.graph.sinkSourceNodes

Interface SourceNode

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    OsmSinkSourceNode, OsmSourceNode

    public interface SourceNode
    Represents a source node that might be used as agent origin, with a given set of destination sink nodes.

    Notice that it is just a convenient way to represent origin / destinations behavior, but agents can freely spawn and disappear anywhere.
